Actors for the Timeliness Tracker System

* FlightStats Web Servers

    These are repositories for all the information regarding the flights. 
    These servers are queried from the user interface to extract the information 
    through an HTTP Request. They extract the data and return to the interface to 
    be presented to the user.

* Airline Company

    It has a pivotal role in this system. The airline company decides and controls 
    the schedule of the flights. The airline company enters the data about the flight 
    i.e. starting point, destination, time, route, delay time. The server data is updated 
    and maintained by the airline company that allows the user to retrieve real-time and 
    consistent information about the flights via the FlighStats web service.

* Federal Aviation Authority (FAA)

    This federal body is responsible for regulating the norms of air travel in the United States. 
    All the policies, protocols are outlined and every airline, airport have to abide by these 
    rules. The system should comply with the rules of the FAA as it provides the information to the 
    user. The rules and policies should be available to be shown to the user if necessary or the 
    user tries to query a restricted information.

* Google Static Maps

    The Google maps provides a view of the flightâ€™s starting point and destination on the United States 
    map. This is to provide an additional flight positional display feature in the system. This helps improve the 
    aesthetics and helps to better visualize the flight details. 

* Weather Database

    The primary cause of delay is unforeseen weather conditions. The database from the weather department 
    helps the application provide the user with the current and projected weather forecast that will help predict 
    a delay in the flight travel. The user can also query the weather forecast before asking for the flight information, 
    if he/she wishes to travel in the week and wishes to make other/alternate travel plans. The system interfaces with 
    the weather database and it informs the user about the projected delay so that he can get to the airport at the right time.

* Traveler

    The traveler is the principal user of the system. He/she has a mobile interface and a web interface to access the 
    system. He/she can query the information of a flight, airport or query about a route. The user selects the flight, airport, etc. 
    according to the information that he/she seeks. The user has or may have a login to save his account information like 
    past travels. The user can choose where to get the information i.e. his mobile interface or his web interface.

* SPARQCode Interface

    The SPARQCode interface reads QR Codes (Quick Response Code) which is a type of matrix barcode (or a two-dimensional bar code). 
    It is basically an optical machine-readable label. The purpose of the QR code is provide access to the web interface via the 
    user's mobile device. It contains a URL encoded within it which the user scans using the camera on his/her smartphone. This 
    ultimately provides the flight details on the user's smartphone. The SPARQ interface on the mobile device understands the 
    QR code and gives the access to the relevant application store (Play Store or iTunes Store) depending on the operating 
    system of the mobile device.
